Group: FedNow Service
Collection: FedNow Service Release 1
Usage Guideline: BusinessApplicationHeader_head.001.001.02
Base Message: head.001.001.02
Date of publication: 01 June 2023
URL: https://www2.swift.com/mystandards/#/mp/mx/_kijaUKEYEeuB-v2uhrZqSw/_qR07WZ5FEeyNX8SYmSuaLA
Description: FedNow Service Scope

The Business Application Header (BAH) provides a bridge between the more technical network envelope and the actual ISO 20022 business message, e.g., the payment instruction.

FedNow Service Usage

The Business Application Header (BAH) is required for all messages sent across the FedNow Service, i.e., value, nonvalue, system, and reporting messages.

A single guideline for usage of the BAH has been defined for FedNow participants and the FedNow Service application. Where needed, differences in usage between FedNow participants and the FedNow Service are captured in specific rules.
Generated by the MyStandards web platform [https://www.swift.com/mystandards] on 2023-06-01T13:54:07+00:00
